    slug: "quebec-road-trip-exotic-car-rental",
    title: "Quebec Road Trip in an Exotic Car: Montreal to Quebec City, Mont-Tremblant and Beyond",
    date: "2026-05-30",
    description: "Take the ultimate Quebec road trip in an exotic car — from Montreal to Quebec City, Mont-Tremblant, and beyond in a Lamborghini, McLaren, or Ferrari.",
    content: "<h2>The Ultimate Quebec Road Trip in an Exotic Car</h2><p>Quebec is one of the most breathtakingly beautiful provinces in Canada, and it contains some of North America finest driving roads. From the sweeping curves of the Laurentian highways to the riverside Route 138 along the St. Lawrence, from the historic streets of Old Quebec City to the ski resort villages of Mont Tremblant, Quebec rewards drivers who bring the right machine to its roads.</p><p>At Exotic Rentals Montreal, we offer multi day rental arrangements specifically designed for Quebec road trip adventures. Load up a Lamborghini Huracán, a Porsche 911 TechArt, or a Ferrari 488 GTB and discover what this magnificent province looks like through the windshield of a world class supercar.</p><h2>Montreal to Quebec City: A Road Trip Worth Savoring</h2><p>The roughly 250 kilometer journey from Montreal to Quebec City along Route 20 or the more scenic Route 138 takes you through some of Quebec most beautiful countryside. The St. Lawrence River appears as a vast inland sea at certain points along the route, and the historic town of Trois Rivieres makes an excellent halfway stop for coffee, fuel, and a walk around the old town.</p><p>Arriving in Old Quebec City in an exotic car is a genuinely theatrical experience. The narrow cobblestone streets of the lower town and the dramatic fortification walls of upper Quebec City create a backdrop unlike anything else in North America. A Porsche 911 TechArt or McLaren 570GT navigating these streets creates images worth framing. Plan for approximately two to three hours of driving time each way, allowing for the inevitable slow downs to appreciate the scenery and take photos.</p><h2>Montreal to Mont Tremblant: The Laurentian Mountain Drive</h2><p>The drive north from Montreal toward Mont Tremblant on the autoroute des Laurentides and then the regional roads into the mountains is one of the most rewarding driving experiences in eastern Canada. The highway provides stretches where the performance of a Lamborghini Huracán or Ferrari 488 GTB can be genuinely explored in a legal and controlled manner.</p><p>As you enter the mountains and transition to the winding regional roads surrounding Mont Tremblant village, the drive becomes a different kind of pleasure. Corners and elevation changes reward precise driving, and the forest scenery in every season from summer green to fall orange to winter white is spectacular. The village of Mont Tremblant itself is a sophisticated resort destination with excellent restaurants, hotels, and leisure activities to fill your multi day stay.</p><h2>The Eastern Townships Loop</h2><p>For a shorter but equally beautiful road trip, the Eastern Townships circuit southeast of Montreal covers some of Quebec most scenic wine country, lake regions, and charming heritage villages. The route from Montreal through Granby, Bromont, Knowlton, Magog, and Sherbrooke forms a natural loop of approximately 300 kilometers with abundant stops worth making.</p><p>The rolling hills and lake vistas of the Eastern Townships look absolutely spectacular from behind the wheel of an Audi RS7 or Porsche 911, and the region excellent restaurants and vineyard destinations make every stop worthwhile.</p><h2>Best Vehicles for Quebec Road Trips</h2><p>For multi day road trips across Quebec, we recommend vehicles that balance performance with grand touring comfort. The Porsche 911 4S TechArt is perhaps our ideal road trip machine, combining effortless highway cruising with the ability to shine on winding mountain roads. Starting at approximately $800 per day.</p><p>The Audi RS6 and RS7 offer exceptional all day comfort alongside their Quattro performance credentials, making them outstanding choices for longer journeys with luggage. Starting at approximately $550 per day. The Ferrari 488 GTB is the most dramatic choice, demanding a bit more driver attention and focus but delivering an unforgettable journey experience unlike anything else. Starting at approximately ];,200 per day.</p><h2>Planning Your Multi Day Rental</h2><p>Multi day rental discounts are available for bookings of two or more consecutive days. Contact our team at 438-809-4417 to discuss pricing for your specific trip duration and vehicle preference. We recommend planning your road trip dates in advance and booking as early as possible, since our most popular vehicles for road trips book out weeks ahead during summer and fall foliage season.</p><p>We can deliver your chosen vehicle to your Montreal home or hotel at the start of your trip and arrange pickup at your return location. For trips that begin or end outside of Montreal, we can discuss delivery and pickup logistics directly. Call 438-809-4417 today and start planning your Quebec exotic car road trip adventure. The open road is waiting, and so is your dream car.</p>",
